# ovh_vps_backup_ftp_access

Manages FTP backup access rules for an OVHcloud VPS.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/resources/vps_backup_ftp_access/example_1.tf"}}

## Argument Reference

The following arguments are supported:

* `service_name` - (Required) The service_name of your VPS.
* `ip_block` - (Required) The IP block to authorize for FTP backup access.
* `ftp` - (Optional) Whether FTP access is enabled for this block.
* `nfs` - (Optional) Whether NFS access is enabled for this block.
* `cifs` - (Optional) Whether CIFS access is enabled for this block.

## Attributes Reference

(See generated docs/resources/vps_backup_ftp_access.md for the full attribute list.)

The following attributes are exported:

* `id` - The ID of the FTP backup access rule.
